Fig. 1
Susceptible Exposed Infectious Recovered (SEIR) disease model used in our simulations to capture the health states of the individuals. Everyone starts out in susceptible state and if infected, moves to the exposed state, followed by one of symptomatic or asymptomatic infectious states, followed by the recovered state. The duration of time spent by an infected individual in the exposed and infectious states is shown in the distributions associated with them
